postcontent: H&K 93 5.56 Rifle made sometime in the 1980s-I was told was on the tail end of importing inthe USA-Has a longer flash with a pin tacked welded on the flash so you cant turn it off with out gringing the weld-They did this because the last ones in the country H&K ran out of standard lenght barrels so they used a shorter barrel and extended the flash to make it legal-They also stamped reciever H&K 93 - H&K 42-with the  SERIAL number-These are very hard to find-Also has a factory Bi-pod-asking 3,500 or best cash offer or trades -This HK93 or HK42 is super RARE - likely rarest and most collectible of ALL 5.56mm or 223 cal HK rifles! At the end of the series run, no more commercial barrels were on-hand, so HK made the last very few HK93 rifles with HK33 Machine Gun Barrels and re-struck them as HK42! That's right - MG barrels The series 42 Hk93s did not all necessarily come with a Hk33 barrel. Some Hk93s with the 42 had standard 1/12 twist barrels suitable for the 55 gr stuff. Some of the 42s had the shorter Hk33 barrel with the longer blind pinned flash hiders to meet the US 16" requirements, but even these came in either 1/12, or 1/7. The 1/7 barrels are marked 178 on the barrel under the handguard. The 1/7 will stabilize the heavier 62 gr and higher ammo. Other than being HK black and not the earlier blue grey they are the same. Unless they have the longer flash hider, and even then don't assume a 1/7. If the barrelThe barrel on my rifle i cant find the 1/78 but it does have the longer pin flash hider
